Lisp:
    1: First to intruduce garbage collection

    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lisp

Stimula:
    2; First Object oriented programming language:
        had everything: inheritance, virtual functions etc

    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simula


Algol 58:
    3: introduced the difference between comparison ans assignment operators
        := assignment, = equality
    
    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ALGOL_58#History

Algol 60:
    4: introduced code blocks using `begin` and `end` keywords

    5: one of the first languages to introduce the dangling-else delima because of
    the removal of the then statmeent to if then blocks

    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ALGOL_58#History


